{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform the national curriculum for drama to include LGBTQ+ and POC stories",
        "additional_details": "Update the curriculum to include LGBTQ+ and POC stories, find inclusive scripts, make it normal to play characters that students can relate to. Why should LGBTQ+ actors always have to change themselves to tell stories they don\u2019t know how to tell and vice versa. Be more inclusive because I have faced more than enough prejudice over my time in education and I hear too many similar stories.",
        "background": "There is a lack of LGBTQ+ and POC representation in the drama curriculum in many schools. Schools should be required to teach drama using more diverse content, there\u2019s no excuses for exclusion.",
